is transforms visual ideas directly into executable code\n\n### 2. **Multi-Model Strategy**\n- GitHub CEO Thomas Dohmke announced that Copilot is moving beyond exclusive reliance on OpenAI's GPT models\n- **Claude 3.5 Sonnet** (from Anthropic) and **Gemini 1.5 Pro** (from Google) are being integrated\n- This shift provides developers with more model choices and flexibility\n\n### 3. **Model Upgrade - GPT-5.3-Codex**\nAccording to sources from February 11-12, 2025:\n- OpenAI's latest code model **GPT-5.3-Codex** began rolling out to Copilot\n- **~25% performance improvement** over GPT-5.2-Codex for agentic coding tasks\n- Significantly reduces execution wait time for complex, long-running workflows\n- Available to Copilot Pro, Pro+, Business, and Enterprise paid users\n- Supports VS Code, GitHub web interface, mobile, CLI, and Coding Agent environments\n- Enterprise administrators need to manually enable the feature in settings\n\n### Context and Significance\n- The GPT-5.3-Codex upgrade is viewed as a direct response to **Anthropic's Claude Opus 4.6**\n- These moves demonstrate GitHub's strategy to maintain its AI coding assistant market leadership through a multi-model approach\n- The updates particularly benefit developers working on architecture design and automated refactoring\n\nThe February 2025 updates represent a significant evolution in GitHub Copilot's capabilities, moving from simple code completion to more sophisticated agentic coding and visual understanding features.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
