025 (v0.50/1.0):**\n- Simplified pricing with unlimited usage for Pro plans\n- **Max Mode** for advanced AI capabilities\n- **Background Agents** for parallel task execution\n- Multi-file editing improvements\n- Multi-codebase workspace support\n\n**May 2025:**\n- **BugBot**: Automatic code review tool for GitHub PRs\n- **Memory function**: Remembers conversation context\n- **MCP configuration** (one-click setup)\n- **Jupyter Notebook support**\n- Visual chat responses with Mermaid charts and Markdown tables\n\n## Key Features Available (as of late 2025)\n\n1. **AI Models Support**: GPT-5, Claude Opus 4.5, Gemini 2.5 Pro\n2. **Composer Mode**: Multi-file simultaneous editing\n3. **Agent Mode**: Up to 8 agents running in parallel\n4. **@Web functionality**: AI can search the web for current information\n5. **Image understanding**: UI screenshot to code conversion\n6. **Context window**: Industry-leading large context support\n\n## Pricing (as of December 2025)\n- **Hobby**: Free\n- **Pro**: $20/month\n- **Pro+**: $60/month\n- **Ultra**: $200/month\n\n---\n\n**Note**: Since we're currently in early 2025, there don't appear to be any official changelogs or new feature announcements specifically for February 2025 yet. For the most up-to-date information, I recommend checking Cursor's [official documentation](https://cursor.sh/docs) or their [release notes](https://cursor.sh/changelog).\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
