      "Based on my search results, I couldn't find specific detailed changelog information for Claude Code updates from **February 2025**. However, I can provide you with what I found about that period and subsequent releases:\n\n## Key Information About February 2025\n\n**Launch Date:**\n- Claude Code officially launched on **February 24, 2025**, alongside Claude 3.7 Sonnet\n- This was noted as the research preview release that expanded Claude Code's audience beyond solo developers\n\n## Important Context\n\n1. **The CHANGELOG:** According to a dev.to article by a developer who tracked all Claude Code releases, the official CHANGELOG was updated **176 times in 2025**, with versions distributed as:\n   - v0.2.x: 37 releases\n   - v1.0.x: 82 releases  \n   - v2.0.x: 57 releases\n\n2. **Major Updates After February 2025:**\n   - **September 29, 2025:** Claude 4.5 Sonnet released with improved SWE-bench scores (77.2%)\n   - **September 30, 2025:** Claude Code 2.0.0 major update featuring:\n     - VS Code extension (Beta)\n     - Checkpoints system (with `/rewind` command)\n     - Enhanced terminal UI\n     - Subagents and Hooks\n     - Usage tracking with `/usage` command\n\n## Recommendations\n\nTo find the specific February 2025 changelog, I suggest:\n\n1. **Check the official GitHub repository** directly (several sources mention: `github.com/anthropics/claude-code`)\n2. **Use the built-in command** if you have Claude Code installed: `/release-notes`\n3. **Visit** the official Anthropic documentation at docs.anthropic.com for detailed version history\n\nThe search results indicate that detailed changelog information is best accessed directly from the official GitHub repository or through the Claude Code CLI itself, rather than being comprehensively documented in web articles."
