on, unified execution, security/test hardening, simplified login, JSON-RPC & MCP interface extensions, terminal interaction optimization\n\n2. **Version 0.23.0 (August 2025):**\n   - Added dynamic model switching functionality\n   - Support for gpt-5 high model selection via `/model` command\n\n### **Major Codex CLI Features (2025):**\n- **Multi-modal support**: Can accept and share images/screenshots directly in CLI\n- **Task tracking**: Uses to-do lists for complex work tracking\n- **Tool integration**: Built-in web search and MCP protocol support\n- **Improved terminal UI**: Better display of tool calls and code diffs\n- **Simplified approval modes**: \n  - Read-only mode\n  - Auto mode (workspace access, external operations require approval)\n  - Full access mode\n- **Session state compression**: For managing long-running sessions\n\n### **Important Note:**\nThe search results don't show any specific changelog for **February 2025**. The Codex CLI was originally released in **April 2025**, so there wouldn't be a February changelog. However, if you're looking for the most recent updates, the September 2025 (v0.36.0) and August 2025 (v0.23.0) releases contain the latest significant changes.\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about any particular aspect of Codex CLI or check for updates from a different time period?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
