%25AD%2591%25E6%25A2%25A6%25E5%25B2%259B/id6465838500\"},{\"title\":\"DKChat AI\",\"url\":\"https://apps.apple.com/in/app/dkchat-ai/id6749002789\"},{\"title\":\"WizChat AI – Everything Speaks\",\"url\":\"https://apps.apple.com/cn/app/wizchat-ai-everything-speaks/id6748057099\"},{\"title\":\"HerAI - Voice Chat AI\",\"url\":\"https://apps.apple.com/tn/app/herai-voice-chat-ai/id1659618925\"},{\"title\":\"HerAI - Voice Chat AI\",\"url\":\"https://apps.apple.com/qa/app/herai-voice-chat-ai/id1659618925\"}]\n\nBased on my search results, I was able to find information about Aider AI coding assistant releases. Here's what I found:\n\n## Aider AI Coding Assistant - Recent Updates\n\n### Latest Known Releases (from GitHub)\n\n**Aider v0.85.0** (Recent release)\nKey highlights include:\n- **New Models**: Added support for Gemini 2.5 models (gemini-2.5-pro, gemini-2.5-flash), OpenAI o3-pro, and Responses API models (o1-pro, o3-pro)\n- **New Features**:\n  - `--add-gitignore-files` flag to add files from .gitignore to editing scope\n  - Co-authored-by attribution now enabled by default for commits\n  - `--commit-language` option to specify commit message language\n  - Enhanced thinking tokens support\n  - Increased max tokens for DeepSeek models to 65536\n- **Repository Map**: Added MATLAB and Clojure language support\n- **Performance**: Optimized chat history summarization\n- Note: \"Aider wrote 21% of the code in this release\"\n\n**Aider v0.84.0** (Previous release)\n- Added support for Claude Sonnet 4 and Opus 4 series\n- Added support for Vertex AI Gemini 2.5 Flash Preview\n- Updated default OpenRouter models (deepseek/deepseek-r1:free for free tier)\n- Automatic GitHub Copilot token refresh\n\n### Important Note About February 2025\n\nI could not find a specific changelog for **February 2025** releases. The search results show:\n\n1. The official GitHub repository (github.com/Aider-AI/aider/releases) would have the most up-to-date release information\n2. The most recent documented releases in my search results are v0.85.0 and v0.84.0\n3. I found a Chinese blog post mentioning \"Aider v0.86.0\" with GPT-5 support, but this appears to be from a potentially unreliable source dated 2026-02-06\n\n### Recommendation\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date changelog information, I recommend:\n1. Visiting the official [Aider GitHub Releases page](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/releases)\n2. Checking the official [Aider website](https://aider.chat/) for announcements\n3. Following Aider's official social media or blog for the latest updates\n\nWould you like me to search for any specific features or aspects of Aider that you're interested in?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
