icle/KGDSLF97055616X8.html\"}]\n\nBased on my web search, I need to clarify something important: **I could not find any specific Gemini CLI updates or changelogs for February 2025.**\n\n## What the Search Results Show\n\nThe search results primarily discuss Gemini CLI releases from **June-July 2025** (not February), which appears to be when the tool was initially launched and received major updates. There also appear to be some search results with dates in early 2026, suggesting the dates in some sources may be incorrect.\n\n## Key Information Found:\n\n### **Initial Launch (June 2025)**\n- Gemini CLI was officially announced by Google in late June 2025\n- Open-source command-line tool based on Gemini 2.5 Pro\n- Free tier: 60 requests/minute, 1,000 requests/day with personal Google account\n\n### **Major Updates Found (Not February-Specific):**\n\n**v0.1.18 (August 2025):**\n- Enhanced Gemini 2.5 Pro usage quotas\n- Multi-directory support with `--include-directories` parameter\n- `/init` command for auto-generating GEMINI.md project files\n- `/chat delete` command\n- Auto-update support\n\n**July 2025 Updates:**\n- Audio and video file support\n- Markdown table rendering\n- Nested Markdown imports using @ symbol\n- `/privacy` command for privacy settings\n- Framework upgrade: Ink 5 → Ink 6, React 19\n- Editor integration: VSCodium and Neovim support\n- \"Shades of Purple\" theme\n\n**v0.22.x (December 2025/January 2026):**\n- Gemini 3 models opened to Free Tier users\n- Conductor and Endor Labs extensions updated\n\n## Recommendation\n\nIf you're looking for the latest Gemini CLI updates, I recommend:\n\n1. **Visit the official GitHub repository**: `https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli`\n2. **Check the Releases page** for official changelogs\n3. **Review the `docs/changelogs/latest.md`** file mentioned in some sources\n\nWould you like me to search for more recent information or specific version numbers you're interested in?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
