            "title": "微软向免费用户开放Copilot Vision，测试显示AI网页助理仍未成熟",
            "url": "https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1827815392872857046"
          },
          {
            "title": "“My productivity is boosted, but …” Demystifying Users' Perception ...",
            "url": "https://arxiv.org/html/2508.12285v1"
          }
        ]
      },
      "Based on my web search results, I found information about GitHub Copilot Vision and user reactions around February 2025. However, I should note an important distinction: **there are two different \"Copilot Vision\" features**, which may cause some confusion:\n\n## What I Found\n\n### 1. **GitHub Copilot Vision (VS Code) - February 2025 Release**\nThe Visual Studio Code February 2025 update (version 1.98) introduced **Copilot Vision** as a new feature that allows users to attach and interact with images in chat prompts. According to the official VS Code release notes:\n- This feature enables image-based interactions in Copilot Chat\n- It was released as part of the broader Copilot updates including Agent Mode, Next Edit Suggestions, and Code Search\n- The feature went through preview stages and is part of GitHub Copilot's evolution\n\n### 2. **Microsoft Copilot Vision (Edge Browser) - User Feedback from March 2025**\nI found more extensive user feedback about **Microsoft's Copilot Vision** feature in Edge (which is different from GitHub's). While this feedback is from March 2025 (just after February), it provides relevant insights:\n\n**User Testing Results (Windows Latest testing, March 2025):**\n- **Status**: Described as \"半成品\" (half-finished/immature product)\n- **Major Issues Reported**:\n  - **Response interruptions**: Copilot would stop mid-response for up to 15 seconds, then suddenly switch answers\n  - **Interaction limitations**: Cannot execute clicks, play videos, or respond to \"stop speaking\" commands\n  - **Narrow scope**: Only recognizes screen-visible content, cannot scroll or track information across pages\n  - **Processing limitations**: Relies on existing text, cannot actively search network data\n  - **Logic inconsistencies**: Gets stuck in loops requiring repeated questions\n\n**User Assessment**: Currently only suitable for extracting basic information, not practical for complex tasks. Testers suggested it needs improvement in core features like scroll browsing and cross-page retrieval.\n\n### 3. **Broader GitHub Copilot User Research**\nA comprehensive academic study from August 2025 analyzed user perceptions of AI coding assistants including GitHub Copilot:\n- **Key finding**: \"My productivity is boosted, but...\" - expressing mixed feelings\n- Users value intelligent suggestions but demand more context-aware, customizable, and resource-efficient interactions\n- Developers may spend over 50% of their coding time verifying AI-generated suggestions, increasing cognitive load\n\n## Limitations of Available Information\n\nI did not find extensive, specific user reactions about **GitHub Copilot's Vision feature** specifically from February 2025. Most of the detailed feedback relates to:\n1. The Microsoft Edge Copilot Vision (different product)\n2. General GitHub Copilot experiences\n3. The broader VS Code 1.98 update announcement\n\nWould you like me to:\n- Search for more specific information about GitHub Copilot Vision in particular?\n- Look for user discussions on platforms like GitHub, Reddit, or developer forums?\n- Focus on the Microsoft Copilot Vision feedback instead?"
    ],
    "durationSeconds": 13.189708801999979
  }
